		╭───────────────────────────────╮
		│ SERVER BUILD SCRIPT FOR GEM++ │
		╰───────────────────────────────╯

This version is intended to be distributed for server use,
where user doesn't have root privileges. GEM++ framework
will be installed in the home directory, and the user will
have to set path to point to the GEM++ distribution in order
to use it.

The script "build.sh" compiles the software and builds a self-
extracting archive that self-installs when extracted.

Here is the obtained installation tree :
~/bin/GEM++
		├── bin/
		│	├── GEM++dist
		│	├── GEM++gui
		│	├── GEM++multidist
		│	├── GEM++multisub
		│	└── GEM++sub
		└─ lib/
			├── libGEM++Cplex.so # GEM++ libs
			├── libGEM++GLPK.so
			├── libGEM++Gurobi.so
			├── libGEM++.so
			├── libicudata.so.51 # Qt libs
			├── libicui18n.so.51
			├── libicuuc.so.51
			├── libQt5Core.so.5
			├── libQt5Gui.so.5
			├── libQt5Widgets.so.5
			└── libQt5XML.so.5
